plainable and justifiable\",30\r\n246,TRANSPARENCY,ICMJE,ICMJE requires authors to disclose the use of AI-assisted technologies at submission,30\r\n172,EDITOR,ACCOUNTABILITY,\"Editors are accountable for ensuring compliance with AI policies in the publication process and for the editorial decisions made based on peer reviews. This dual responsibility underscores their critical role in upholding both ethical standards in AI integration and the integrity of the peer review system. As key stakeholders in academic publishing, editors serve as intermediaries between authors, reviewers, and publishers, balancing technical, ethical, and procedural considerations. Their accountability extends to maintaining transparency and fairness in decision-making, particularly as AI tools increasingly influence aspects of manuscript evaluation and content curation. This highlights the evolving nature of editorial roles in response to advancements in artificial intelligence and the need for robust governance frameworks to guide their application.\",29\r\n344,CONFIDENTIALITY,EMERALD,\"Emerald enforces confidentiality in the peer review process, prohibiting the use of AI tools to evaluate submitted materials\",28\r\n296,AUTHORSHIP,ICMJE,\"ICMJE emphasizes that AI tools cannot be listed as authors, and authors are fully responsible for their work\",27\r\n373,ACCOUNTABILITY,EMERALD,Emerald holds authors and itself accountable for the ethical and responsible use of AI tools in publishing,23\r\n410,DATA,EMERALD,\"Emerald prohibits the use of generative AI tools to manipulate or report research data, ensuring its authenticity and integrity\",22\r\n456,DATA PRIVACY,EMERALD,Emerald ensures compliance with data privacy laws when using AI tools in academic publishing,20\r\n458,REVIEWER,EMERALD,Emerald has policies that govern how reviewers interact with AI tools during the peer review process,18\r\n419,RESEARCH,EMERALD,Emerald requires that research conducted using AI tools maintains originality a